---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';

const updated = '2026-06-14';
---

<Base
    title="Privacy & Cookie Policy | Kids Disease"
    description="How Kids Disease handles data: a static educational site with optional, consent-based Google Analytics, no accounts, no ads, and no collection of health data. Full cookie list and your choices explained."
>
    <Breadcrumbs items={[{ name: 'Home', href: '/' }, { name: 'Privacy Policy' }]} />

    <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-8 py-8 space-y-6">
        <header class="space-y-1">
            <h1 class="text-2xl md:text-4xl font-black text-slate-800 dark:text-[#F1EDFF] tracking-tight">Privacy &amp; Cookie Policy</h1>
            <p class="text-[10px] font-black uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-500 dark:text-[#8B84B8]">Last updated: {updated}</p>
        </header>

        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-night-card rounded-3xl border border-orange-100 dark:border-night-line shadow-premium p-6 md:p-8 space-y-6 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-[#D8D2F5] font-medium leading-relaxed">
            <section class="space-y-2">
                <h2 class="text-base font-black text-slate-800 dark:text-[#F1EDFF]">The short version</h2>
                <p class="text-xs md:text-sm">
                    Kids Disease is a free, static educational website. We have no user accounts,
                    show no ads, and never collect health information about you or your child. The
                    only optional data activity is <strong>Google Analytics</strong>, which counts
                    visits so we can see which pages are useful — and it runs <strong>only if you
                    choose “Accept”</strong> on the cookie banner. If you decline, no analytics
                    cookies are set and the site works exactly the same.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-2">
                <h2 class="text-base font-black text-slate-800 dark:text-[#F1EDFF]">Cookies and local storage we use</h2>
                <p class="text-xs md:text-sm">
                    Two small items are stored on your own device to make the site work — these are
                    strictly necessary and never sent anywhere. Analytics cookies are set
                    <strong>only after you accept</strong> them.
                </p>
                <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                    <table class="w-full text-[11px] md:text-xs border-collapse">
                        <thead>
                            <tr class="text-left border-b border-orange-100 dark:border-night-line">
                                <th class="py-2 pr-3 font-black text-slate-800 dark:text-[#F1EDFF]">Name</th>
                                <th class="py-2 pr-3 font-black text-slate-800 dark:text-[#F1EDFF]">Type</th>
                                <th class="py-2 pr-3 font-black text-slate-800 dark:text-[#F1EDFF]">Purpose</th>
                                <th class="py-2 font-black text-slate-800 dark:text-[#F1EDFF]">Set when</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody class="align-top">
                            <tr class="border-b border-orange-50 dark:border-night-line/60">
                                <td class="py-2 pr-3"><code>kidsdisease-theme</code></td>
                                <td class="py-2 pr-3">Local storage (necessary)</td>
                                <td class="py-2 pr-3">Remembers your light/dark theme choice.</td>
                                <td class="py-2">Always · stays on your device</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr class="border-b border-orange-50 dark:border-night-line/60">
                                <td class="py-2 pr-3"><code>kidsdisease-consent</code></td>
                                <td class="py-2 pr-3">Local storage (necessary)</td>
                                <td class="py-2 pr-3">Remembers your cookie choice so we don't ask again.</td>
                                <td class="py-2">After you choose · stays on your device</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="py-2 pr-3"><code>_ga</code>, <code>_ga_&lt;id&gt;</code></td>
                                <td class="py-2 pr-3">Cookie (analytics)</td>
                                <td class="py-2 pr-3">Google Analytics — counts visits and distinguishes sessions.</td>
                                <td class="py-2">Only after you click “Accept” (up to ~2 years)</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-2">
                <h2 class="text-base font-black text-slate-800 dark:text-[#F1EDFF]">Analytics (Google Analytics 4)</h2>
                <p class="text-xs md:text-sm">
                    With your consent, we use Google Analytics 4 (provided by Google Ireland/LLC) to
                    understand aggregate traffic — for example, how many people visit, which pages
                    they read, the approximate country, and the general device or browser type. This
                    helps us improve the most-used content.
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1.5 text-xs md:text-sm">
                    <li>Google Analytics 4 <strong>does not store your IP address</strong>; it is used only briefly to estimate country, then discarded.</li>
                    <li>We have <strong>not</strong> enabled Google Signals, advertising features, or ad personalisation.</li>
                    <li>We never upload anything you type — searches and the triage checker run entirely in your browser (see below).</li>
                    <li>Google processes this data under its own terms. See
                        <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener" target="_blank" class="text-brand-teal hover:underline">Google's Privacy Policy</a>,
                        <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" rel="noopener" target="_blank" class="text-brand-teal hover:underline">how Google uses data</a>, and the optional
                        <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" rel="noopener" target="_blank" class="text-brand-teal hover:underline">browser opt-out add-on</a>.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-2">
                <h2 class="text-base font-black text-slate-800 dark:text-[#F1EDFF]">Your choices</h2>
                <p class="text-xs md:text-sm">
                    Analytics is entirely your choice. You can <strong>Accept</strong> or
                    <strong>Decline</strong> on the banner shown on your first visit. You can change
                    your mind at any time using the <strong>“Cookie preferences”</strong> link in the
                    footer — choosing Decline afterwards disables Google Analytics and clears its
                    cookies. You can also block or delete cookies in your browser settings.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-2">
                <h2 class="text-base font-black text-slate-800 dark:text-[#F1EDFF]">Health information &amp; what we never do</h2>
                <p class="text-xs md:text-sm">
                    We do <strong>not</strong> collect, store, or transmit any health information
                    about you or your child. The symptom triage checker and the search box run
                    entirely inside your browser — your answers and search terms are never sent to
                    us or to anyone else, and they disappear when you leave the page. We have no user
                    accounts, no forms that submit data to us, no advertising, and we never sell data.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-2">
                <h2 class="text-base font-black text-slate-800 dark:text-[#F1EDFF]">Service providers &amp; third parties</h2>
                <p class="text-xs md:text-sm">
                    To deliver the site, your browser necessarily contacts a few providers, which
                    receive your IP address and request details as a normal part of serving web
                    pages (this is required for any website to load and is not used to track you):
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1.5 text-xs md:text-sm">
                    <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — hosting and content delivery (the site runs on Cloudflare Pages). See <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" rel="noopener" target="_blank" class="text-brand-teal hover:underline">Cloudflare's privacy policy</a>.</li>
                    <li><strong>Google Fonts</strong> — web fonts, and <strong>Cloudflare cdnjs</strong> — icon files.</li>
                    <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> — only with your consent, as described above.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-2">
                <h2 class="text-base font-black text-slate-800 dark:text-[#F1EDFF]">Legal basis &amp; your rights</h2>
                <p class="text-xs md:text-sm">
                    Where the GDPR / UK GDPR applies: analytics relies on your <strong>consent</strong>
                    (which you can withdraw at any time), and the providers needed to deliver the page
                    rely on our <strong>legitimate interest</strong> in serving a working, secure
                    website. You have the right to access, correct, erase, or object to processing of
                    your personal data, and to lodge a complaint with your data-protection authority.
                    Because we hold no personal data ourselves, requests about analytics data are
                    handled through Google's controls and your browser; for anything else,
                    <a href="/contact/" class="text-brand-teal hover:underline">contact us</a>.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-2">
                <h2 class="text-base font-black text-slate-800 dark:text-[#F1EDFF]">International transfers</h2>
                <p class="text-xs md:text-sm">
                    Our providers (Cloudflare, Google) operate globally and may process data outside
                    your country, including in the United States, under their own safeguards such as
                    the EU Standard Contractual Clauses and the EU–US Data Privacy Framework.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-2">
                <h2 class="text-base font-black text-slate-800 dark:text-[#F1EDFF]">Children's privacy</h2>
                <p class="text-xs md:text-sm">
                    Kids Disease is written for parents and caregivers and is not directed at
                    children. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children. Any analytics
                    data is aggregate and not used to identify individuals.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-2">
                <h2 class="text-base font-black text-slate-800 dark:text-[#F1EDFF]">Changes &amp; contact</h2>
                <p class="text-xs md:text-sm">
                    If what we collect ever changes, we will update this page and revise the date
                    above before the change takes effect. Questions or concerns?
                    <a href="/contact/" class="text-brand-teal hover:underline">Contact us</a>.
                </p>
            </section>
        </div>
    </article>
</Base>
